name: NYDailyNews
text:
Upstate New Yorkers received an urgent message on their phones nearly 19 years to the minute terrorists flew two planes into the WTC.

An official for the Buffalo suburb of Tonawanda said the unfortunately timed alert was the result of a “training error."
https://t.co/fr4aKWtUbl

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Several students at Ohio's Miami University hosted a party AFTER testing positive for coronavirus.

“Aren’t you supposed to be quarantining?” an officer asked one of the infected students.
 “Yeah, that’s why I’m at my house," he replied.
https://t.co/fV88GTuFjD

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Wondering why the hashtag #CancelNetfix is trending?

It's all because of "Cuties," a French film described by critics as an "oversexualization of children in a way that adds to the problem of child sexual exploitation."
https://t.co/dmHAW2Qez5

name: NYDailyNews
text:
About 19 million Americans tuned in to watch the “Thursday Night Football” season opener pitting the Houston Texans vs. Kansas City Chiefs.

That's a 13% drop in ratings from the 2019 Opening Night matchup between the Green Bay Packers and Chicago Bears.
https://t.co/RlQbMXs86Y
